{
  "texts": [
    "In doing so, we note that the progression of DDSP methods in speech synthesis commenced with mixed approaches, integrating DSP components to neural audio synthesisers and benefiting from the strengths of both.",
    "Early examples included the incorporation of LPC synthesis filters (Juvela et al., 2019; Valin and Skoglund, 2019), effectively \"offloading\" part of the synthesis task.",
    "Conversely, the dominant applications of DDSP to music tend to offload all signal generation to differentiable DSP components.",
    "We note that there may be opportunities for both fields to benefit from one another's findings here, exploring further intermediate hybrid approaches.",
    "Hybrid methods, in general, combine the aforementioned strengths of DDSP with more general deep learning models."
  ]
}